# [MS-PST] §3.9 — Sample BTH (inside the §3.8 HN)
# Source: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/openspecs/office_file_formats/ms-pst/f706a5a7-14ff-4fb0-bc3c-2ed7955de13d
#
# Per spec text: "This example uses the same binary dump from the last
# example to further examine the inner BTH structure." So the .bin produced
# from this file is BYTE-IDENTICAL to spec_sample_hn.bin. We keep both files
# only because the user-facing test names ([golden_spec_hn], [golden_spec_bth])
# describe different oracle layers.
#
# BTH layout pulled from the same 258-byte HN dump:
#   BTHHEADER at HN offset 0x0C (8 bytes — first allocation):
#     bType      = 0xB5 (kBthSignature)
#     cbKey      = 0x02   (2-byte keys)
#     cbEnt      = 0x06   (6-byte data per entry)
#     bIdxLevels = 0x00   (leaf-only BTH)
#     hidRoot    = 0x00000040 (entries at HN HID 0x40 = second allocation)
#
#   BTH leaf records at HN offset 0x14 (88 bytes — second allocation):
#     11 records, each (2-byte key + 6-byte data) = 8 bytes:
#       record  0: key=0x0E34 data=0x010002000000A0
#       record  1: key=0x0E38 data=0x000003000000  (wait — see below)
#       (full decode is M4's job; we just pin the bytes here)
#
# IMPORTANT: §3.9 dump is the same physical block as §3.8. No BLOCKTRAILER
# is included. CRC self-consistency check is N/A.
0000000000004800  EC 00 EC BC 20 00 00 00-00 00 00 00 B5 02 06 00
0000000000004810  40 00 00 00 34 0E 02 01-A0 00 00 00 38 0E 03 00
0000000000004820  00 00 00 00 F9 0F 02 01-60 00 00 00 01 30 1F 00
0000000000004830  80 00 00 00 DF 35 03 00-89 00 00 00 E0 35 02 01
0000000000004840  C0 00 00 00 E3 35 02 01-00 01 00 00 E7 35 02 01
0000000000004850  E0 00 00 00 33 66 0B 00-01 00 00 00 FA 66 03 00
0000000000004860  0D 00 0E 00 FF 67 03 00-00 00 00 00 22 9D B5 0A
0000000000004870  DC D9 94 43 85 DE 90 AE-B0 7D 12 70 55 00 4E 00
0000000000004880  49 00 43 00 4F 00 44 00-45 00 31 00 01 00 00 00
0000000000004890  F5 5E F6 66 95 69 CC 4C-83 D1 D8 73 98 99 02 85
00000000000048A0  01 00 00 00 00 00 00 00-22 9D B5 0A DC D9 94 43
00000000000048B0  85 DE 90 AE B0 7D 12 70-22 80 00 00 00 00 00 00
00000000000048C0  22 9D B5 0A DC D9 94 43-85 DE 90 AE B0 7D 12 70
00000000000048D0  42 80 00 00 00 00 00 00-22 9D B5 0A DC D9 94 43
00000000000048E0  85 DE 90 AE B0 7D 12 70-62 80 00 00 08 00 00 00
00000000000048F0  0C 00 14 00 6C 00 7C 00-8C 00 A4 00 BC 00 D4 00
0000000000004900  EC 00
